{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}

'''Yang Metal Tiger also known as 甲午 (kanoetora, koukinnotora, kouin)''' is one of the [[Sexagenary cycle]].

It is the 27th combination in the Sexagenary cycle; the preceding combination is {{ill|Jichū|ja|己丑}} and the following combination is {{ill|Xinyou|ja|辛卯}}. In the system of [[陰陽五行思想]] (Yin-Yang and the Five Elements), the [[十干]] element {{ill|Jia|ja|甲}} represents yang [[木]] (Wood) and the [[十二支]] element {{ill|Tiger|ja|寅}} represents yang [[火]] (Fire), and they interact by [[五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|Mutual Overcoming]] (Metal overcomes Wood).

== Years of Kōgo ==
A year in the [[Common Era]] that leaves a remainder of 30 when divided by 60 is a year of Kōgo.
