{{infobox Chinese|l=Yang Metal Tiger|kanji=庚寅|romaji=kanoe tora|onyomi=kōin|p=gēngyín|w=keng-yin|mi=kɤŋ⁵³ ȵin²¹|y=geng1 jan4|j=geng1 jan4|ci=kɪŋ jɐn|mc=kæŋ ŋin|oc-bs=kˤraŋ ŋin|qq=}}
{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive|qq=}}

'''Yang Metal Tiger also known as 甲午 (kanoetora, koukinnotora, kouin)''' is one of the [[Sexagenary cycle]].

It is the 27th combination in the Sexagenary cycle; the preceding combination is {{ill|Jichū|ja|己丑|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} and the following combination is {{ill|Xinyou|ja|辛卯|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}. In the system of [[陰陽五行思想]] (Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory), the [[十干]] element {{ill|Jia|ja|甲|1=Kinoe (甲)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} represents yang [[木]] (Wood) and the [[Earthly Branches]] element {{ill|Tiger|ja|寅|1=Tiger (zodiac)|lt=Tiger (寅)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} represents yang [[火]] (Fire), and they interact by [[五行思想#相剋（そうこく）|Mutual Overcoming]] (Metal overcomes Wood).

== Years of Kōgo ==
A year in the [[Common Era]] that leaves a remainder of 30 when divided by 60 is a year of Kōgo.
